      "content": "thanks. i actually have a scanned copy of the 1947 Accord of Kalsan which outlines the succession rights. it basically proves that the regency remains a sovereign entity even if the borders were redrawn by the soviets. if i were to present this to a foreign ministry or a UN subcommittee, what kind of specific legal frameworks should i lead with to make sure they don't just dismiss it as a historical curiosity? i need them to see it as a valid active sovereignty claim.",
